This paper deals with event coreference resolution, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of Bayesian models and distance functions suggests a focus on machine learning and statistical methods, which are common in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of feature-rich distance functions may suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
